BOJ’s Shirakawa Says Japan’s Economic Activity Is Picking Up

-- B y   T o r u   F u j i o k a
-- 
2011-10-20T00:34:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/boj-s-shirakawa-says-japan-s-economic-activity-is-picking-up.html
Bank of Japan (8301)  Governor Masaaki
Shirakawa said the nation’s economic activity is picking up.  He also said the BOJ needs to watch developments in the
European sovereign debt crisis because uncertainties remain.
Shirakawa spoke to a meeting of branch managers of the central
bank in  Tokyo  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Toru Fujioka in Tokyo at 
